        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: reject bridge tickets in query strings",
        "body": "Closes #688.\n\nSummary:\n- stop accepting live bridge agent tickets from URL query strings by default\n- keep the dedicated bridge-ticket header and bearer-token transports\n- add a temporary legacy compatibility flag for operators that still need query-ticket clients during rollout\n- update WebVNC, Code, and portal docs and add WebVNC, code, and egress regressions\n\nUpgrade context: current CLI bridge paths send tickets outside the URL. Coordinators reject query-ticket clients by default; operators that need a temporary legacy rollout can set `CRABBOX_ALLOW_QUERY_BRIDGE_TICKETS=1` while affected clients upgrade.\n\nProof: live coordinator WebSocket output is posted in https://github.com/openclaw/crabbox/pull/746#issuecomment-4850630665.\n",
